https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JFF2vJaN0Cw&list=PLxCzCOWd7aiGFBD2-2joCpWOLUrDLvVV_

Neso Academy
Comprehensive tutorials on networking fundamentals, including theoretical and practical insights.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VwN91x5i25g&list=PLBlnK6fEyqRgMCUAG0XRw78UA8qnv6jEx

Eli the Computer Guy
Explains complex computer networking topics in simple and understandable terms.
https://www.youtube.com/user/elithecomputerguy

Hussein Nasser
Focused on advanced networking and system design, including real-world scenarios.
https://www.youtube.com/@hnasr/featured

Sunny Classroom
Simplified lessons on networking concepts, ideal for beginners.
https://www.youtube.com/user/sunnylearning

Certbros
Networking tutorials designed for certification preparation like CCNA and CompTIA.
https://www.youtube.com/c/Certbros

Online Courses
Computer Networking (Coursera)
A comprehensive introduction to networking principles, including TCP/IP and wireless networking.
https://www.coursera.org/learn/computer-networking

Grokking Computer Networking (Educative.io)
An interactive course explaining networking concepts from the basics to advanced topics.
https://www.educative.io/courses/grokking-computer-networking

Online Websites
Geeks for Geeks
A detailed guide to networking basics, protocols, and advanced topics.
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/basics-computer-networking/

IBM Networking Basics
Overview of computer networking components, protocols, and architectures.
https://www.ibm.com/topics/networking

Wikiversity
Open educational resource covering the basics of computer network components.
https://en.wikiversity.org/wiki/Basic_computer_network_components

Books
Computer Networks by Andrew S. Tanenbaum and David J. Wetherall
A comprehensive textbook covering theoretical and practical aspects of networking.
https://www.amazon.com/Computer-Networks-Andrew-S-Tanenbaum/dp/0130661023

Networking Essentials by Keith Barker and Gary A. Donahue
A practical guide for understanding networking concepts, ideal for certifications like CCNA.
https://www.amazon.com/Networking-Essentials-Keith-Barker/dp/1587204414

Simulation Tools
Ns-3
A discrete-event network simulator used for academic and research purposes.
https://www.nsnam.org/

OMNeT++
A versatile simulation tool for modeling and simulating networks.
https://omnetpp.org/

Research Papers
Computer Networks (ACM Digital Library)
Access to the latest research and articles on networking concepts and innovations.
https://dl.acm.org/loi/cnet

Networking Research (IEEE Xplore)
A repository of high-quality research papers in computer networking.
https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/browse/journals/page/journals/toc/toc.cnet
